# Migration and Deployment Walkthrough

We have successfully completed all task items to migrate the database connection to Supabase and prepare the Express REST API for Vercel Serverless deployment.

---

## Changes Made

### 1. Database Configuration
Updated [db.js](file:///a:/antigravity/website/src/config/db.js) to dynamically support a single connection string `DATABASE_URL` (preferred for Supabase connection pooling) alongside individual parameters (used for local Docker setup). Added standard SSL configuration (`ssl: { rejectUnauthorized: false }`) which is mandatory for Supabase.

### 2. Express Serverless Lifecycle
Adapted [app.js](file:///a:/antigravity/website/src/app.js) to be fully serverless-friendly:
- Wrapped the local listener `app.listen()` inside a check `if (require.main === module)`. When deployed on Vercel, the file is required as a library and will not listen on ports, preventing serverless execution blocks or crashes.
- Implemented a lazy initialization middleware that automatically sets up database tables on the very first incoming request (cold start) if they haven't been created yet, bypassing subsequent checks.

### 3. Vercel Serverless Function Handler
Created a new entrypoint [api/index.js](file:///a:/antigravity/website/api/index.js) that exports the Express `app`. Vercel automatically wraps this export in a serverless function handler.

### 4. Vercel Routing Rules
Created [vercel.json](file:///a:/antigravity/website/vercel.json) in the workspace root to define rewrites:
- API routes `/api/:path*` and `/health` map directly to the backend handler `/api/index.js`.
- Static files at root `/` and general resources `/index.css` / `/app.js` serve files statically from the `/public` folder.

