## How to Deploy to Vercel & Supabase

### Phase 1: Set up Supabase
1. Create a project in [Supabase](https://supabase.com).
2. Go to **SQL Editor**, paste the SQL from [db/init.sql](file:///a:/antigravity/website/db/init.sql), and run it to set up the tables and indexes.
3. Go to **Project Settings -> Database** and copy the **URI Connection String** under connection pooling (using port `6543`).

### Phase 2: Deploy to Vercel
1. Ensure the Vercel CLI is installed, or hook up your GitHub repository to Vercel.
2. In the Vercel dashboard, create a new project and import this repository.
3. Add the following **Environment Variables** in Vercel:
   - `DATABASE_URL`: `postgresql://postgres.[YOUR_PROJECT]:[PASSWORD]@aws-0-us-east-1.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?pgbouncer=true&sslmode=require`
   - `DB_SSL`: `true`
   - `GITHUB_TOKEN`: `[Your GitHub Personal Access Token]` (Optional, but recommended to prevent API rate limiting)
4. Click **Deploy**. Vercel will build and serve your static frontend and route API calls to the serverless function.
5. Verify the deployment by testing the health check `/health` on your live URL.
